 ('13', '97', '2', '1', 'en_us', 'Draft 1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Poggio La Noce Wine dinner in Napoli Italy, March 28th, 2015\",\"slug\":\"poggio-la-noce-wine-dinner-in-napoli-italy-march-28th-2015\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>We spend a lot of time doing tastings and wine dinner events which tend to be mostly in the US. So it was a nice change to do a wine dinner down in Naples, especially because it turned out to be such a fun lively evening with a great crowd of wine lovers.  A big Thank You to Rosi and Nicola for organizing this!<\\/p><p>                                  <img style=\\\"width: 333px; height: 149.6px;\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.poggiolanoce.com\\/images\\/pages\\/tasting-the-wines-small.jpg#asset:96\\\" unselectable=\\\"on\\\"><\\/p>\",\"25\":\"\",\"2\":\"\"}}', '2015-04-14 16:50:46', '2015-04-14 16:50:46', '3aec6c6b-042e-4bb5-83f1-65b9b56f9b23'),
 ('14', '97', '2', '1', 'en_us', 'Draft 2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Poggio La Noce Wine dinner in Naples, Italy, March 28th, 2015\",\"slug\":\"poggio-la-noce-wine-dinner-in-napoli-italy-march-28th-2015\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"\",\"25\":\"\",\"2\":\"\"}}', '2015-04-14 16:51:28', '2015-04-14 16:51:28', '66a02a19-b364-46e7-b527-ca199858c9d5'),
 ('15', '127', '2', '1', 'en_us', 'Draft 1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Winter ground cover or also known as green mulching...\",\"slug\":\"winter-ground-cover-or-also-known-as-green-mulching\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Last fall we planted a mixture of leguminoseae and gramineae seeds; peas, fave and oats and planted these every second row in the vineyard. We do this because these plants are nitrogen fixing, so that when we cut them down in the spring time and mulch them back into the ground we\'re basically providing green natural fertilizer. Not to mention that in the spring time the vineyard looks stunning with all the colours from the flowers popping up everywhere.<\\/p>\",\"25\":[\"126\"],\"2\":\"\"}}', '2015-04-30 17:27:42', '2015-04-30 17:27:42', 'f70f01c4-28c7-442a-887f-18d974be41c2'),
 ('17', '187', '2', '1', 'en_us', 'Draft 1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gigi\\u00f2 2012 scores with Antonio Galloni!\",\"slug\":\"gigi\\u00f2-2012-scores-with-antonio-galloni\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>We are very pleased to announce that Gigi\\u00f2 2012 was reviewed by Antonio Galloni of Vinous.com and that it scored 91 points. <\\/p><p>But even nicer, were his comments :<em> \\\"An unusual blend of Sangiovese and Teroldego, the 2012 Gigi\\u00f2 is also one of the most <strong data-redactor-tag=\\\"strong\\\">intriguing <\\/strong>wines I tasted in Tuscany this year. Dark stone fruits, graphite and smoke are all given an extra kick of energy and delineation as this <strong>explosive <\\/strong>red shows off its <strong>distinctive personality<\\/strong>.\\\"<\\/em><span><\\/span><\\/p>\",\"25\":\"\",\"2\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-09 08:54:34', '2016-04-09 08:54:34', '881a9068-c600-417d-a188-c1ea65ea20b5'),
