 ('349', '44', '3', '1', 'en_us', '20', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vineyard & Winery\",\"slug\":\"vineyard\",\"postDate\":1421257380,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"45\":{\"type\":\"banner\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bannerHeadline\":\"The Vineyard & the Winery\",\"bannerImage\":[\"53\"]}}},\"7\":\"<h2>The Winery<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 11px;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; line-height: 105%; font-family: \\\"Times New Roman\\\",serif; font-size: 12pt;\'><font color=\\\"#000000\\\">The recently completed Poggio La Noce winery is built\\r\\nentirely underground right into the hillside below our beautiful olive grove.\\r\\nThis makes it especially energy efficient and helps maintain the ideal\\r\\ntemperature and humidity for our wines throughout the year.<\\/font><\\/span><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 11px;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; line-height: 105%; font-family: \\\"Times New Roman\\\",serif; font-size: 12pt;\'><font color=\\\"#000000\\\">Because of our limited production, our winery is\\r\\nappropriately sized and is optimized for small scale \\u2013 high quality\\r\\nVinification. Its design allows everything to be well integrated and within\\r\\neasy reach, for a natural work flow, from initial harvest to final bottling of\\r\\nthe wine.<\\/font><\\/span><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<span style=\'margin: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 105%; font-family: \\\"Times New Roman\\\",serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>The winery also includes a modern,\\r\\norganic and state of the art tasting area, where visitors can enjoy tasting our\\r\\nwines. Thanks to large sliding windows, the tasting room is naturally\\r\\nintegrated with its surrounding landscape, with stunning views of our valley\\r\\nand the vineyards.<\\/span><\\/p><h2>\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Vineyard<\\/h2><p>The vineyard is situated at about 800 feet elevation facing, South-South West, giving it perfect sun exposure from morning to evening. It sits on a hillside with steep incline providing good drainage and the soil is a mix of shaley clay with Albarese and Galestro limestone.<br><\\/p><p>This hillside is proving to be a very special terroir for the Sangiovese grape, yielding beautiful fresh lively and elegant Sangiovese based wines with huge depth and good longevity potential. <\\/p>\",\"12\":[\"64\"],\"6\":\"The estate\",\"26\":{\"231\":{\"type\":\"photoGallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"galleryTitle\":\"The Winery\",\"galleryDescription\":\"Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed.\",\"galleryImages\":\"\",\"galleryPageInclude\":\"1\"}}}}}', '2016-11-11 18:46:17', '2016-11-11 18:46:17', '85715cb2-a47a-44ed-8334-4482762ec5cd'),
 ('350', '44', '3', '1', 'en_us', '21', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vineyard & Winery\",\"slug\":\"vineyard\",\"postDate\":1421257380,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"45\":{\"type\":\"banner\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bannerHeadline\":\"The Vineyard & the Winery\",\"bannerImage\":[\"53\"]}}},\"7\":\"<h2>The Winery<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The recently completed Poggio La Noce winery is built\\r\\nentirely underground right into the hillside below our beautiful olive grove.\\r\\nThis makes it especially energy efficient and helps maintain the ideal\\r\\ntemperature and humidity for our wines throughout the year.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Because of our limited production, our winery is\\r\\nappropriately sized and is optimized for small scale \\u2013 high quality\\r\\nVinification. Its design allows everything to be well integrated and within\\r\\neasy reach, for a natural work flow, from initial harvest to final bottling of\\r\\nthe wine.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\r\\nThe winery also includes a modern,\\r\\norganic and state of the art tasting area, where visitors can enjoy tasting our\\r\\nwines. Thanks to large sliding windows, the tasting room is naturally\\r\\nintegrated with its surrounding landscape, with stunning views of our valley\\r\\nand the vineyards.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Vineyard<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The vineyard is situated at about 800 feet elevation facing, South-South West, giving it perfect sun exposure from morning to evening. It sits on a hillside with steep incline providing good drainage and the soil is a mix of shaley clay with Albarese and Galestro limestone.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This hillside is proving to be a very special terroir for the Sangiovese grape, yielding beautiful fresh lively and elegant Sangiovese based wines with huge depth and good longevity potential. <\\/p>\",\"12\":[\"274\"],\"6\":\"The estate\",\"26\":{\"231\":{\"type\":\"photoGallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"galleryTitle\":\"The Winery\",\"galleryDescription\":\"Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed.\",\"galleryImages\":\"\",\"galleryPageInclude\":\"1\"}}}}}', '2016-11-11 19:23:10', '2016-11-11 19:23:10', '16987d3d-46f3-44aa-8901-a829013939e8'),
 ('351', '275', '5', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gig\\u00edo 2012\",\"slug\":\"gig\\u00edo-2012\",\"postDate\":1479248987,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"50\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"numericalAward\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineScore\":\"93\",\"awardSponsor\":\"Wine Spectator\"}}},\"47\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quoteBody\":\"Lots of dried-berry, burnt-orange & dark-chocolate aromas. Full body, juicy tannins and a spicy, coffee, walnut and berry aftertaste. Needs time to soften. A blend of 90% sangiovese and 10% merlot. Better in 2016\",\"quoteAuthor\":\"James Suckling\"}}},\"22\":[\"58\"]}}', '2016-11-15 22:29:47', '2016-11-15 22:29:47', '9fa070c9-b3c0-4a3f-9547-53619fcad8b4'),
 ('352', '42', '3', '1', 'en_us', '14', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"About\",\"slug\":\"about\",\"postDate\":1421257320,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"43\":{\"type\":\"banner\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bannerHeadline\":\"Learn More About Us\",\"bannerImage\":[\"52\"]}}},\"7\":\"<h2>The Poggio La Noce Estate<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tThe estate was founded by husband and wife team, Enzo Schiano and Claire Beliard, in 2000. Nestled in the hills of Fiesole, Tuscany, facing south\\/south-west, the property sits in some of the most beautiful countryside just outside Florence, amidst hills sprinkled with medieval bell towers and castle ruins.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tThe property consists of one vineyard (5 acres) cultivated with mostly Sangiovese grapes and a small percentage of Teroldego, in a mix of older vines (15 years+) and younger ones (8 years+). The vineyard thanks to its small size and human dimension is cared for maniacally making it a real jewel.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tFrom the beginning, we set out to farm organically and have been certified organic since 2006.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Our Team<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tHusband and wife, Enzo Schiano and Claire Beliard are the owners of the Poggio la Noce estate. Enzo is Italian and Claire is French. They share the vision and love for making great wines.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tRoberto Corti is the Poggio la Noce estate Manager. Roberto studied agronomy at the university of Florence and cares for all aspects of the vineyard work as well as that of the cellar, and manages the wine making along with Claire and Enzo.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Ilaria di Mattia is the Sales and Marketing Manager. A professional sommelier, Ilaria joined Poggio La Noce last year, and has since worked assiduously at helping develop sales channels for our young winery.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tOur consulting team is made up of Valentino Ciarla, our technical oenologist, as well as Stefano Dini and GianLuca Grassi, who are our agronomists.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>And of course all this under the careful guardianship of our beloved Maremmano Shepard dog, Marcellino. <\\/p><p><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/67.205.142.46\\/\\/images\\/pages\\/IMG_1543smallweb.jpg#asset:267\\\"><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Our Philosophy<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can make a new section by cutting and pasting the headline from an above section, then simply adding content below it.<\\/p>\",\"12\":\"\",\"6\":\"Learn more about us\",\"26\":{\"256\":{\"type\":\"photoGallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"galleryTitle\":\"Test About\",\"galleryDescription\":\"Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua\",\"galleryImages\":[\"75\",\"93\",\"94\"],\"galleryPageInclude\":\"1\"}}}}}', '2016-11-17 09:11:12', '2016-11-17 09:11:12', '9880af45-bc18-4806-8fd7-85c9defa80b4'),
