echnical oenologist, as well as Stefano Dini and GianLuca Grassi, who are our agronomists.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And of course all this under the careful guardianship of our beloved Maremmano Shepard dog, Marcellino. <\\/p>\",\"12\":[\"284\",\"323\"],\"6\":\"Learn more about us\",\"26\":{\"256\":{\"type\":\"photoGallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"galleryTitle\":\"The Team\",\"galleryDescription\":\"Pictures of the Poggio La Noce Team members\",\"galleryImages\":[\"294\",\"295\",\"296\",\"297\",\"298\",\"299\"],\"galleryPageInclude\":\"1\"}},\"304\":{\"type\":\"photoGallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"galleryTitle\":\"Marcellino\",\"galleryDescription\":\"Our Maremma sheep dog, guarding the winery and the family\",\"galleryImages\":[\"300\",\"301\",\"302\",\"303\",\"305\"],\"galleryPageInclude\":\"1\"}}}}}', '2016-11-27 10:31:30', '2016-11-27 10:31:30', 'a2dc16f9-1c2d-4ad9-b493-278ec28e20dc'),
 ('387', '44', '3', '1', 'en_us', '26', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vineyard & Winery\",\"slug\":\"vineyard\",\"postDate\":1421257380,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"45\":{\"type\":\"banner\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bannerHeadline\":\"The Vineyard & the Winery\",\"bannerImage\":[\"53\"]}}},\"7\":\"<h2>The Winery<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The recently completed Poggio La Noce winery is built\\r\\nentirely underground right into the hillside below our beautiful olive grove.\\r\\nThis makes it especially energy efficient and helps maintain the ideal\\r\\ntemperature and humidity for our wines throughout the year.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Because of our limited production, our winery is\\r\\nappropriately sized and is optimized for small scale \\u2013 high quality\\r\\nVinification. Its design allows everything to be well integrated and within\\r\\neasy reach, for a natural work flow, from initial harvest to final bottling of\\r\\nthe wine.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThe winery also includes a modern,\\r\\norganic and state of the art tasting area, where visitors can enjoy tasting our\\r\\nwines. Thanks to large sliding windows, the tasting room is naturally\\r\\nintegrated with its surrounding landscape, with stunning views of our valley\\r\\nand the vineyards.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\nThe Vineyard<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The vineyard is situated at about 800 feet elevation facing, South-South West, giving it perfect sun exposure from morning to evening. It sits on a hillside with steep incline providing good drainage and the soil is a mix of shaley clay with Albarese and Galestro limestone.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This hillside is proving to be a very special terroir for the Sangiovese grape, yielding beautiful fresh lively and elegant Sangiovese based wines with huge depth and good longevity potential. <\\/p><h2>Our Philosophy<\\/h2><p>You can make a new section by cutting and pasting the headline f