 ('419', '44', '3', '1', 'en_us', '36', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vineyard & Winery\",\"slug\":\"vineyard\",\"postDate\":1421257380,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"45\":{\"type\":\"banner\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bannerHeadline\":\"The Vineyard & the Winery\",\"bannerImage\":[\"53\"]}}},\"7\":\"<p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>The Winery<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The recently completed Poggio La Noce winery is built\\r\\nentirely underground right into the hillside below our beautiful olive grove.\\r\\nThis makes it especially energy efficient and helps maintain the ideal\\r\\ntemperature and humidity for our wines throughout the year.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Because of our limited production, our winery is\\r\\nappropriately sized and is optimized for small scale \\u2013 high quality\\r\\nVinification. Its design allows everything to be well integrated and within\\r\\neasy reach, for a natural work flow, from initial harvest to final bottling of\\r\\nthe wine.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThe winery also includes a modern,\\r\\norganic and state of the art tasting area, where visitors can enjoy tasting our\\r\\nwines. Thanks to large sliding windows, the tasting room is naturally\\r\\nintegrated with its surrounding landscape, with stunning views of our valley\\r\\nand the vineyards.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\nThe Vineyard<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The vineyard is situated at about 800 feet elevation facing, South-South West, giving it perfect sun exposure from morning to evening. It sits on a hillside with steep incline providing good drainage and the soil is a mix of shaley clay with Albarese and Galestro limestone.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This hillside is proving to be a very special terroir for the Sangiovese grape, yielding beautiful fresh lively and elegant Sangiovese based wines with huge depth and good longevity potential. <\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Our Philosophy<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Our work begins in the vineyard and carries beyond. We are driven by our love for great wine and we set out from the very beginning with an uncompromising eye for detail to produce the most beautiful, healthy grapes, thus yielding the best possible wine this terroir can enable. Our commitment to achieve excellence begins in the vineyard, where we tend to each vine individually. The vines are weeded, hoed, pruned, leaves and fruit are cut back, grape bunches are thinned in continuation as may be required.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The same level of dedication and focus carries over to the cellar where the wine is made. We harvest manually and carry the fruit in small trays to the destemmer. Even before the fruit goes to the destemmer, grape clusters are selected on the first sorting table, prying open each cluster to check for immature berries and imperfections that can develop inside of each closed cluster. After this first quality selection, the individual berries roll onto a second sorting table where several people check for additional berry imperfections. Only perfect fruit will make it to the fermentation tanks. This is for all the wines we produce, not just our top wine.<\\/p>\",\"12\":[\"274\",\"325\"],\"6\":\"The estate\",\"26\":{\"313\":{\"type\":\"photoGallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"galleryTitle\":\"The winery\",\"galleryDescription\":\"La nostra nuova Cantina\",\"galleryImages\":[\"306\",\"307\",\"308\",\"309\",\"310\",\"311\",\"312\"],\"galleryPageInclude\":\"1\"}},\"319\":{\"type\":\"photoGallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"galleryTitle\":\"Poggio La Noce vineyard\",\"galleryDescription\":\"I nostri viti\",\"galleryImages\":[\"314\",\"315\",\"316\",\"317\",\"318\",\"320\",\"321\",\"322\"],\"galleryPageInclude\":\"1\"}}}}}', '2016-11-27 16:55:54', '2016-11-27 16:55:54', 'e7d4adc5-ce09-4ce6-ba16-b188dfaa8af5'),
