 ('471', '275', '5', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gig\\u00edo 2012\",\"slug\":\"gig\\u00edo-2012\",\"postDate\":1479248940,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"50\":{\"276\":{\"type\":\"numericalAward\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineScore\":\"93\",\"awardSponsor\":\"Wine Spectator\",\"awardUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/poggiolanoce.com\"}}},\"47\":{\"277\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quoteBody\":\"Lots of dried-berry, burnt-orange & dark-chocolate aromas. Full body, juicy tannins and a spicy, coffee, walnut and berry aftertaste. Needs time to soften. A blend of 90% sangiovese and 10% merlot. Better in 2016\",\"quoteAuthor\":\"James Suckling\"}}},\"22\":[\"58\"]}}', '2016-12-05 19:00:22', '2016-12-05 19:00:22', '93a8b59d-9c4a-49a7-a04e-f476ff2d0e7e'),
 ('472', '48', '3', '1', 'en_us', '27', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Contact\",\"slug\":\"contact\",\"postDate\":1421257560,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"49\":{\"type\":\"banner\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bannerHeadline\":\"Get in touch\",\"bannerImage\":[\"73\"]}}},\"7\":\"<h2>How to reach us<\\/h2>\\r\\n<iframe src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/maps\\/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d58129.93243744846!2d11.370236447956291!3d43.78779223369125!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x132baad566a47839%3A0x37a833dd8b34d006!2sPoggio+La+Noce!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1478811195558\\\" width=\\\"900\\\" height=\\\"450\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" style=\\\"border:0\\\" allowfullscreen=\\\"\\\"><\\/iframe>\\r\\n<p>Using Googlemap enter \\\"Poggio La Noce\\\".<br>Otherwise reach the village of Montebeni, Fiesole. Once there, follow Via Ontignano till the bottom of the valley. When you reach the unpaved section of the road, the road climbs for roughly two hundred yards, after which you will see the entrance to the estate with a sign \\\"Poggio La Noce\\\".&nbsp;If you need assistance, please call us at 055 654 9113.<br>GPS coordinates: Lat. 43.796735, Long. 11.345128.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Winery Visits<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The New Poggio La Noce winery is open for visits and tastings, just 15 minutes from the center of Florence!<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Poggio La Noce is a small, intimate wine estate and we offer a unique and personal tasting experience. The visit will include a walk through our vineyard as well as a tour of our brand new winery.&nbsp; The visit will be followed by a tasting of all our wines accompanied with light snacks.&nbsp; Cost of the visit and tasting: 15 Euro per person.&nbsp; <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>By appointment only, so please email or call us before hand.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Email Us<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Contact us by filling out the following information<br><\\/p>\",\"12\":[\"75\",\"332\"],\"6\":\"Contact us\",\"26