 ('44', 'field', '7', 'en_us', ' the winery the recently completed poggio la noce winery is built entirely underground right into the hillside below our beautiful olive grove this makes it especially energy efficient and helps maintain the ideal temperature and humidity for our wines throughout the year because of our limited production our winery is appropriately sized and is optimized for small scale high quality vinification its design allows everything to be well integrated and within easy reach for a natural work flow from initial harvest to final bottling of the wine the winery also includes a modern organic and state of the art tasting area where visitors can enjoy tasting our wines thanks to large sliding windows the tasting room is naturally integrated with its surrounding landscape with stunning views of our valley and the vineyards the vineyard the vineyard is situated at about 800 feet elevation facing south south west giving it perfect sun exposure from morning to evening it sits on a hillside with steep incline providing good drainage and the soil is a mix of shaley clay with albarese and galestro limestone this hillside is proving to be a very special terroir for the sangiovese grape yielding beautiful fresh lively and elegant sangiovese based wines with huge depth and good longevity potential our philosophy our work begins in the vineyard and carries beyond we are driven by our love for great wine and we set out from the very beginning with an uncompromising eye for detail to produce the most beautiful healthy grapes thus yielding the best possible wine this terroir can enable our commitment to achieve excellence begins in the vineyard where we tend to each vine individually by hand the same level of dedication and focus carries over to the cellar where the wine is made we harvest manually and carry the fruit back to the winery where all grape clusters are selected on a first sorting table the individual berries are then selected on a second sorting table where several people check for any possible berry imperfection only perfect fruit will make it to the fermentation tanks this is for all the wines we produce not just our top wine '),
