 ('88', 'field', '1', 'en_us', ' getting ready for spring and summer so what do we do bottle our rose monday morning we bottled pinko pallino because 2014 was such a difficult year we ended up with little rose we stored it in the smaller vat with the addition of the cooling plate to maintain temperature at below 12 degrees celcius this year we had a lot of fun making pinko pallino because we ended doing a blend of gigio bled off juice and early harvest grapes specifically for rose with its own white wine like vinification meaning that you press the bunches right away our bottling operation is still artisanal but it works juice flows from the vat to a small filter to the bottling machine into the bottles which then are immediately corked with the remaining air getting pumped out we then let the bottles rest 24 hours standing up to allow the corks to expand and after that they re moved to our temperature controlled cellar to rest on their sides until we ship out we did get to taste it though yum '),
